)@@G@@ $J IRLNK3  @]@@@^ .          @]@@@^ .          @C@@@^IRLNK1 . SET DOES QB
)@@G@@NOT HAVE MORE THAN ONE LINK   @E@@@^          LA,H1     A1,GSETPKT     .QC
)@@G@@ $P SET TYPE TO A1      @E@@@^          JZ        A1,LNKDONE      . $T TQD
)@@G@@YPE WAS NEXT      @E@@@^          ER        ERR$           . $A YES,LNKDQE
)@@G@@ONE NO,EXIT @]@@@^ .          @]@@@^ .          @G@@@^LNKDONE . CHECK IFQF
)@@G@@ SET OWNER HAS A PRIOR POINTER TO LINK. FOR EXAMPLE:  @E@@@^        . SEQG
)@@G@@T THAT IS LINKED NEXT WITH ORDER LAST           @]@@@^        .   @A@@@^QH
)@@G@@          LX        X8,AENTAD      .@E@@@^          LA,S5     A1,0,X8   QI
)@@G@@     . $P SET TYPE TO A1      @E@@@^          TNZ       A1             .QJ
)@@G@@ $T SET TYPE IS NEXT    @E@@@^          J         LNKGT6         . $A YEQK
)@@G@@S,LNKGT6 NO       @E@@@^          TE,U      A1,010         . $T SET TYPEQL
)@@G@@ IS OWNER   @E@@@^          J         LNKDONE1          . $A NO,LNKDONE1QM
)@@G@@ YES  @]@@@^ .          @C@@@^ . GET NEXT RECORD TO RDA TO CHECK ON TYPEQN
)@@G@@      @]@@@^ .          @]@@@^LNKGT6 .    @E@@@^          LA        A0,NQO
)@@G@@EXTDBP     . $P NEXT DBP TO A0      @G@@@^          SLJ       DBPGET    QP
)@@G@@     . $W DBPGET READ NEXT RECORD TO RDA  @G@@@^          LA,H2     A0,SQQ
)@@G@@ETCPKT+2   . $P ADDR OF SET CUR TBL TO A0       @G@@@^          LA,T2   QR
)@@G@@  A2,0,A0        . $P RECORD CODE OF SET OWNER TO A2  @G@@@^          TEQS
)@@G@@,T1     A2,RDA+2       . $T WAS NEXT RECORD THE SET OWNER   @E@@@^      QT
)@@G@@    J         LNKDONE1       . $A NO,LNKDONE1 YES     @C@@@^ . CALL GETSQU
)@@G@@ET TO FIND LINK TYPE OF OWNER       @A@@@^          LA,U      A0,RDA    QV
)@@G@@      @G@@@^          SA,H1     A0,SETCPKT+1   . $P UPDATE RECORD ADDRESQW
)@@G@@S IN SETCPKT@E@@@^          LA,H2     A0,SETCPKT     . $P SET CODE TO A0QX
)@@G@@      @G@@@^          LA        A1,SETCPKT+1   . $P ADDR OF RECORD TO H1QY
)@@G@@ OF A1      @G@@@^                                   .    RECORD CODE TOQZ
)@@G@@ T3 OF A1         @E@@@^          TNZ,H1    C9             .    NEW SCHERA
)@@G@@MA          @^@@@^          J         $+3 @G@@@^          LA,U      A2,2RB
)@@G@@           . $P SCHEMA INDICATOR TO A2          @A@@@^          J       RC
)@@G@@  IRGT55          @^@@@^          LA,U      A2,1@]@@@^IRGT55 .    @]@@@^RD
)@@G@@ .          @G@@@^          SLJ       GETSET         . $W GETSET GET SETRE
)@@G@@ POINTERS         @A@@@^          JP        A1,$+2          @^@@@^      RF
)@@G@@    ER        ERR$@G@@@^          SSL       A0,18          .    GET RID RG
)@@G@@OF LOWER PART OF A0     @E@@@^          TE,U      A0,01          . $T ISRH
)@@G@@ LINK TYPE PRIOR  @E@@@^          J         LNKDONE1       . $A NO,LNKDORI
)@@G@@NE1 YES     @]@@@^ .          @G@@@^          LA        A5,INSDBP      .RJ
)@@G@@ $P DBP OF INSERTED RECORD TO A5    @G@@@^          SA        A5,1,A1   RK
)@@G@@     . DBP OF INSERTED RECORD TO OWNER    @A@@@^          LA,U      A0,RRL
)@@G@@DA         .@G@@@^          SLJ       TFCHANGE       . $W TFCHANGE  CHANRM
)@@G@@GE TEMP FILE      @G@@@^          SLJ       RBUFUPD           . $W RBUFURN
)@@G@@PD UPDATE REC BUF       @]@@@^ .          @G@@@^LNKDONE1 . UPDATE CURRENRO
)@@G@@CY OF SET INTO WHICH AN INSERT JUST OCCURED     @]@@@^       .    @G@@@^RP
)@@G@@          LX,H2     X8,SETCPKT+2   . $P ADDR OF SET CUR TBL ENTRY TO X8 RQ
)@@G@@@E@@@^          LA,H2     A0,SETCPKT     . $P SET CODE TO A0      @G@@@^RR
)@@G@@          LA        A1,IRCODE      . $P INSERTED RECORD CODE TO A1      RS
)@@G@@@E@@@^          TE,T1     A0,0,X8        . $  SET CODES EQUAL     @E@@@^RT
)@@G@@          ER        ERR$           .    NO,INTERNAL ERROR   @G@@@^      RU
)@@G@@    SA,T3     A1,0,X8        . $P UPDATE SET CURRENCY RECORD CODE @C@@@^RV
)@@G@@          LA        A2,1,X8           .         @G@@@^          SA      RW
)@@G@@  A2,2,X8           . $P PUSH DBP OF OLD CURRENT DOWN @A@@@^          LARX
)@@G@@        A2,INSDBP      .@G@@@^          SA        A2,1,X8        . $P UPRY
)@@G@@DATE DBP FOR CURRENT OF SET   @E@@@^          J         LNKEXT          RZ
)@@G@@  . $J LNKEXT           @]@@@^ .          @]@@@^/           @]@@@^ .    SA
)@@G@@      @C@@@^ . INSERT AREA CONTROL RECORD WORKER ROUTINE    @A@@@^ . SYNSB
)@@G@@TAX:     ICTL AREA AREA-NAME  @A@@@^ .        OR   ICTL AREA VARIABLE   SC
)@@G@@@]@@@^ .          @E@@@^ . AN AREA CONTROL RECORD WILL BE INSERTED AFTERSD
)@@G@@ THE CURRENT@^@@@^ . TEMPORARY FILE LINE. @C@@@^ . AREA CONTROL RECORD FSE
)@@G@@ORMAT IS AS FOLLOWS:    @]@@@^ .          @E@@@^ . ---------------------SF
)@@G@@-------------------------           @E@@@^ . :                   000000 SG
)@@G@@                  :           @E@@@^ . :--------------------------------SH
)@@G@@------------:           @E@@@^ . :      01      :              :     02 SI
)@@G@@      :           @E@@@^ . :---------------------:----------------------SJ
)@@G@@:           @E@@@^ . :                     :  AREA-CODE           :     SK
)@@G@@      @E@@@^ . :--------------------------------------------:           SL
)@@G@@@]@@@^ .          @C@@@^ . X10 POINTS TO PACKET GENERATED BY THE PARSER SM
)@@G@@@^@@@^ . A0 HAS PACKET TYPE   @]@@@^ .          @]@@@^ .          @]@@@^SN
)@@G@@ICTLA .     @A@@@^          TZ,H2     2,X10          .@G@@@^          J SO
)@@G@@        ERROR75        . NO INDEX ALLOWED ON AREA-NAME      @C@@@^      SP
)@@G@@    TNZ       2,X10             .         @C@@@^          J         ERROSQ
)@@G@@R75           .         @G@@@^          LX,H1     X8,2,X10       . $P ADSR
)@@G@@DR OF SYMBOL TAB ENTRY        @E@@@^          LA,S4     A1,0,X8        .SS
)@@G@@ $P SYMBOL TYPE         @E@@@^          TE,U      A1,020         . $T ISST
)@@G@@ SYMBOL UNDEFINED @E@@@^          J         $+2            . $A NO  YES,SU
)@@G@@ICANAME     @A@@@^          J         ICANAME        .@G@@@^          TESV
)@@G@@,U      A1,017         . $T IS SYMBOL DEFINED PIC X         @E@@@^      SW
)@@G@@    ER        ERR$           . $A NO,EXIT YES         @]@@@^ .          SX
)@@G@@@E@@@^ . SYMBOL IS DEFINED AND AREA NAME IS ENTERED AS A VARIABLE @C@@@^SY
)@@G@@ . SHOULD HAVE THE VALUE AS THE AREA NAME       @G@@@^ . PREPARE TO CALLSZ
)@@G@@ GETVAR FOR AREA NAME, X10 HAS ADDR TO SYMB TAB ENTRY @G@@@^ .          TA
)@@G@@                       . X10 HAS SYMBOL TABLE ENTRY ADDR    @C@@@^      TB
)@@G@@    LX        X10,X8            .         @G@@@^          SZ        A0  TC
)@@G@@           . A0 HAS 0 SINCE ITEM CANNOT BE INDXD@C@@@^          SLJ     TD
)@@G@@  GETVAR         . UPON RETURN@G@@@^                                   .TE
)@@G@@ X10 HAS SYMBOL TABLE ENTRY ADDR    @E@@@^                              TF
)@@G@@     . A0  HAS CHRACTER LENGTH@G@@@^                                   .TG
)@@G@@ A1 ABSOLUTE WORD ADDR OF ITEM      @G@@@^                              TH
)@@G@@     .    + ERROR CODE IF ANY ( BIT 35 )  @G@@@^                        TI
)@@G@@           . A2 CHARACTER OFFSET (1-6)          @E@@@^                  TJ
)@@G@@                 . A3 TYPE,   1 - PIC X   @E@@@^                        TK
)@@G@@           .            2 - PIC 9   @G@@@^                              TL
)@@G@@     .            3 - PIC 9 COMP          @E@@@^          JN        A1,GTM
)@@G@@ETER1      . $T SUCCESSFUL          @E@@@^                              TN
)@@G@@     . $A NO,GETER1 YES       @E@@@^          TE,U      A3,01          .TO
)@@G@@    BETTER BE PIC X ITEM@A@@@^          ER        ERR$           .@A@@@^TP
)@@G@@                                   .@A@@@^                              TQ
)@@G@@     .@G@@@^                                   . GET THE ITEM NAME POINTTR
)@@G@@ED TO BY A  @A@@@^                                   .@G@@@^          TGTS
)@@G@@,U      A0,13          . NAME SHOULD FIT WITHIN 2 WORDS     @G@@@^      TT
)@@G@@                             . SINCE IT IS AN AREA NAME           @A@@@^TU
)@@G@@          J         ERROR77        .@G@@@^          JZ        A0,ERROR77TV
)@@G@@     . NAME CANNOT CONSIST OF 0 CHARACTERS@G@@@^          DS        A0,GTW
)@@G@@VARSAVE    . $P SAVE REGISTERS FROM GETVAR      @A@@@^          DS      TX
)@@G@@  A2,GVARSAVE+2  .@G@@@^          DL        A2,0,A1        . $P TWO WORDTY
)@@G@@S RETURNED TO A2,A3     @A@@@^          LA,U      A0,7           .@G@@@^TZ
)@@G@@          ANA       A0,GVARSAVE+2  . $P ( 7 - OFFSET )*6 TO A0          UA
)@@G@@@C@@@^          MSI,U     A0,6              .         @G@@@^          DSUB
)@@G@@L       A2,0,A0        . $P FIRST WORD OF AREA-NAME TO A3   @E@@@^      UC
)@@G@@    SA        A3,ICTLAN      . $P FIRST WORD TO ICTLAN@E@@@^          LAUD
)@@G@@        A0,GVARSAVE    . $P # OF CHARS TO A0    @E@@@^          TG,U    UE
)@@G@@  A0,7           . $T # OF CHARS > 6      @E@@@^          J         ICTLUF
)@@G@@GT1        . $A YES,ICTLGT1 NO      @]@@@^ .          @G@@@^ .          UG
)@@G@@                         AREA CODE IS ONE WORD OR LESS      @]@@@^ .    UH
)@@G@@      @A@@@^          LA,U      A1,6           .@G@@@^          ANA     UI
)@@G@@  A1,A0          . $P (6- NO OF CHARS) TO A1          @G@@@^          LRUJ
)@@G@@        R1,A1          . $P # OF SPACES TO ADD TO R1        @E@@@^      UK
)@@G@@    LX,U      X9,ICTLAN      . $P ADDR OF WORD TO X9  @C@@@^          SLUL
)@@G@@J       ADDSPCS        . $W ADDSPCS @]@@@^ .          @G@@@^ .          UM
)@@G@@                         FIRST WRD OF 2 WRD ENTRY IS READY  @G@@@^ .    UN
)@@G@@                               PREPARE TO ADD SPACES TO 2ND WORD  @A@@@^UO
)@@G@@          LR        R2,SPACES      .@G@@@^          SR        R2,1,X9   UP
)@@G@@     . $P SPACES TO SECOND WORD           @C@@@^          J         ANREUQ
)@@G@@ADY        . $J ANREADY @]@@@^ .          @C@@@^ICTLGT1                 UR
)@@G@@           . $H         @G@@@^                                   . AREA US
)@@G@@NAME MORE THAN 6 CHARS        @G@@@^          LA        A1,GVARSAVE+1  .UT
)@@G@@ ADDR OF VAR RETURNED BY GETVAR     @G@@@^          DL        A2,1,A1   UU
)@@G@@     . $P 2ND & 3RD WORD FROM GETVAR TO A2@C@@@^                        UV
)@@G@@           .    AND A3  @A@@@^          LA        A0,GVARSAVE+2  .@I@@@^UW
)@@G@@          ANA,U     A0,1           . $P DOUBLE SHIFT LEFT BY (OFFSET -1)UX
)@@G@@*6          @C@@@^          MSI,U     A0,6              .         @A@@@^UY
)@@G@@          LDSL      A2,0,A0        .@G@@@^          SA        A2,ICTLAN+UZ
)@@G@@1    . $P 2ND WORD OF AREA NAME           @A@@@^                        VA
)@@G@@           .@G@@@^          LA        A0,GVARSAVE    . PROCEED TO FILL UVB
)@@G@@P WITH SPACES     @A@@@^          LA,U      A1,12          .@G@@@^      VC
)@@G@@    ANA       A1,A0          . $P (12-NO OF CHARS) TO A1          @G@@@^VD
)@@G@@          LR        R1,A1          . $P # OF SPACES TO FILL TO R1       VE
)@@G@@@G@@@^          LX,U      X9,ICTLAN+1    . $P ADDR OF 2ND WORD TO X9    VF
)@@G@@      @E@@@^          ANA,U     A0,6           . $P REL CHAR POS TO A0  VG
)@@G@@@C@@@^          SLJ       ADDSPCS        . $W ADDSPCS @]@@@^ .          VH
)@@G@@@C@@@^ANREADY                            . $H         @G@@@^            VI
)@@G@@                       . AREA NAME SHOULD BE READY IN ICTLAN@G@@@^      VJ
)@@G@@                             . SEARCH C3 TABLE FOR AREA NAME      @A@@@^VK
)@@G@@          TNZ,H1    C3             .@A@@@^          J         ERROR68   VL
)@@G@@      @E@@@^          LXM,H2    X8,C3          . $P C3 ADDR TO X8       VM
)@@G@@@G@@@^          LXI,U     X8,9           . $P IN CREMENT VALUE TO X8    VN
)@@G@@      @G@@@^          ANX,U     X8,9           . $P X8 POINTS ONE ENTRY VO
)@@G@@LENGTH BEFOR@E@@@^          DL        A2,ICTLAN      . $P AREA NAME TO AVP
)@@G@@2,A3  @G@@@^          LA,H1     A0,C3          . $P # OF WORDS IN C3 TABVQ
)@@G@@LE TO A0    @G@@@^          DSL       A0,36          . $P PREPARE TO DIVVR
)@@G@@IDE BY # OF WORDS @C@@@^          DI,U      A0,9           .    IN ENTRYVS
)@@G@@@E@@@^          TZ        A1             . $P REMAINDER TO A1     @G@@@^VT
)@@G@@          ER        ERR$           .    REMAINDER BETTER BE NONZERO     VU
)@@G@@@G@@@^          LR        R1,A0          . $P # OF ENTRIES IN C3 TABLE TVV
)@@G@@O R1  @G@@@^ANSLP1    SE        A2,10,*X8      . $T FOUND 1ST WORD IN TAVW
)@@G@@BLE         @E@@@^          J         ERROR76        . $A NO,ANNFOUND YEVX
)@@G@@S     @G@@@^          TE        A3,2,X8        . $P FOUND 2ND WORD IN TAVY
)@@G@@BLE         @E@@@^          J         ANSLP1         . $A NO,ANSLP1 YES VZ
)@@G@@      @]@@@^ .          @G@@@^ .                                   AREA WA
)@@G@@NAME FOUND IN C3 TABLE        @E@@@^ .                                  WB
)@@G@@ X8 POINTS TO AREA ENTRY@]@@@^ .          @]@@@^ .          @E@@@^      WC
)@@G@@    LA,T1     A0,0,X8        . $P AREA CODE TO A0     @G@@@^          LSWD
)@@G@@SL      A0,24          . $P GET RID OF HIGH ORDER BITS      @A@@@^      WE
)@@G@@    SSL       A0,24          .@G@@@^          SA,H2     A0,CNTRCD+2    .WF
)@@G@@ $P AREA CODE TO CNTRCD+2           @A@@@^          LA        A1,(01,0,0WG
)@@G@@2)   .@G@@@^          SA        A1,CNTRCD+1    . $P SET UP CNTRCD+1 TO (WH
)@@G@@1,0,2)      @]@@@^DOINSERT    @G@@@^ .                                  WI
)@@G@@ PREPARE TO INSERT CONTROL RECORD   @G@@@^ .                            WJ
)@@G@@       AFTER CURRENT LINE GIVEN BY LN     @]@@@^ .          @]@@@^ .    WK
)@@G@@      @E@@@^          LA        A2,LN          . $P LINE # TO A2        WL
)@@G@@@G@@@^          SA        A2,IPKT        . $P CURRENT LINE # TO IPKT    WM
)@@G@@      @G@@@^          LA,U      A3,3           . $P LENGTH OF CONTROL REWN
)@@G@@C (3) TO A3 @G@@@^          SA,H2     A3,IPKT+2      . $P LENGTH OF CONTWO
)@@G@@ROL REC TO IPKT   @C@@@^          LX,U      X9,CNTRCD      . $          WP
)@@G@@@G@@@^          SX        X9,IPKT+1      . $P ADDR OF CONTROL RECORD TO WQ
)@@G@@IPKT+1@]@@@^ .          @G@@@^ .                                   CALL WR
)@@G@@TEMP FILE ACCESS METHOD       @]@@@^ .          @E@@@^          LX,U    WS
)@@G@@  X10,IPKT       . $P ADDR OF IPKT TO X10 @G@@@^          LMJ       X11,WT
)@@G@@TF$IA      . $W TF$IA CALL TEMP FILE ACCESS METH@A@@@^          TZ,T1   WU
)@@G@@  2,X10          .@A@@@^          ER        ERR$           .@A@@@^      WV
)@@G@@    LA        A0,IPKT        .@E@@@^          SA        A0,LN          .WW
)@@G@@ $P UPDATE LINE NUMBER  @C@@@B          SZ        STATUS            .   WX
)@@G@@      @A@@@^          LX        X10,X10SAV     .@C@@@^          J       WY
)@@G@@  *RETURN        . $E EXIT    @]@@@^ .          @C@@@^ICANAME .         WZ
)@@G@@                 . $H         @]@@@^ .          @E@@@^ .                XA
)@@G@@                   SYMBOL IS UNDEFINED,   @G@@@^ .                      XB
)@@G@@             NAME OF THE VARIABLE IS AREA NAME  @G@@@^ .                XC
)@@G@@                   X8 POINTS TO SYMBOL TABLE ENTRY    @E@@@^          ANXD
)@@G@@X,U     X8,5           . $P BACK UP 5 WORDS     @G@@@^          DL      XE
)@@G@@  A2,0,X8        . $P NAME OF VARIABLE SUPPOSED       @E@@@^          DSXF
)@@G@@        A2,ICTLAN      .    TO BE AN AREA NAME  @C@@@^          J       XG
)@@G@@  ANREADY        . $J ANREADY @]@@@^/           @C@@@^ . INSERT DIRECT CXH
)@@G@@ONTROL RECORD WORKING ROUTINE @C@@@^ . SYNTAX:     ICTL DIRECT NUMERIC NXI
)@@G@@UMERIC      @C@@@^ .             ICTL DIRECT NUMERIC VARIABLE     @C@@@^XJ
)@@G@@ .             ICTL DIRECT VARIABLE NUMERIC     @C@@@^ .             ICTXK
)@@G@@L DIRECT VARIABLE VARIABLE    @]@@@^ .          @G@@@^ . THE FIRST OPERAXL
)@@G@@ND  OF THE COMMAND SPECIFIES THE PAGE NUMBER          @G@@@^ . THE SECONXM
)@@G@@D OPERAND OF THE COMMAND SPECIFIES THE RECORD NUMBER        @C@@@^ . DIRXN
)@@G@@ECT CONTROL RECORD FORMAT IS AS FOLLOWS   @]@@@^ .          @E@@@^ . ---XO
)@@G@@-------------------------------------------           @E@@@^ . !        XP
)@@G@@          000000                    !           @E@@@^ . !--------------XQ
)@@G@@------------------------------!           @E@@@^ . !     04       !     XR
)@@G@@         !     02       !           @E@@@^ . !--------------------------XS
)@@G@@------------------!           @E@@@^ . !      PAGE NUMBER     !   RECORDXT
)@@G@@ NUMBER     !           @E@@@^ . !--------------------------------------XU
)@@G@@------!           @]@@@^ .          @C@@@^ . X10 POINTS TO PACKET GENERAXV
)@@G@@TED BY THE PARSER @^@@@^ . A0 HAS PACKET TYPE   @]@@@^ .          @]@@@^XW
)@@G@@ .          @]@@@^ICTLD .     @G@@@^          AX,U      X10,2          .XX
)@@G@@ $P X10 POINTS TO ENTRY OF 1ST OPER @G@@@^          SLJ       ICTGVAR   XY
)@@G@@     . $W ICTGVAR GET VARIABLE OR NUMERIC @G@@@^                        XZ
)@@G@@           . $ UPON RETURN, A0 WILL HAVE NUMBER @G@@@^                  YA
)@@G@@                 . $ X10 WILL POINT TO NEXT ENTRY     @G@@@^            YB
)@@G@@                       .   FIRST OPERAND IS THE PAGE NUMBER @A@@@^      YC
)@@G@@    TG        A0,(01000000)  .@A@@@^          J         ERROR80        .YD
)@@G@@@G@@@^          SA,H1     A0,CNTRCD+2    . $P PAGE NUMBER TO CNTRCD+2,,HYE
)@@G@@1     @G@@@^          SLJ       ICTGVAR        . $W ICTGVAR GET 2ND VARIYF
)@@G@@ABLE OR NUM @A@@@^          TG        A0,(010000)    .@A@@@^          J YG
)@@G@@        ERROR80        .@G@@@^          S,H2      A0,CNTRCD+2    . $P REYH
)@@G@@CORD NUMBER TO CNTRCD+2,,     @A@@@^          LA,U      A1,04          .YI
)@@G@@@G@@@^          SA,T1     A1,CNTRCD+1    . $P SPECIAL CODE 4 TO CNTRCD+1YJ
)@@G@@,,T1  @C@@@^          J         DOINSERT       . $J DOINSERT@]@@@^/     YK
)@@G@@      @]@@@^ .          @]@@@^ .          @]@@@^ .          @E@@@^ . SUBYL
)@@G@@ROUTINE TO MODIFY THE RECORD BUFFER OF A RECORD       @E@@@^ . TYPE WHICYM
)@@G@@H IS CURRENTLY IN RDA IF THE RECORD IN RDA HAS  @C@@@^ . THE SAME DBP ASYN
)@@G@@ THAT IN THE RECORD BUFFER.   @]@@@^ .          @]@@@^ .          @]@@@^YO
)@@G@@ .          @C@@@^RBUFUPD   +         0                 . $H      @]@@@^YP
)@@G@@ .          @]@@@^ .          @C@@@^ . FIRST SEARCH RECORD SEQUENCE TABLYQ
)@@G@@E           @]@@@^ .          @]@@@^ .          @E@@@^          LA,T1   YR
)@@G@@  A2,RDA+2          . $P RECORD CODE TO A2@G@@@^          LR,H1     R1,TYS
)@@G@@T1            . $P RECORD COUNT TO R1           @G@@@^          LX,H2   YT
)@@G@@  X9,TT1            . $P ADDR OF SEQUENCE TABLE TO X9 @C@@@^          LXYU
)@@G@@I,U     X9,1              .         @G@@@^          SE,T1     A2,,*X9   YV
)@@G@@        . $T IS RECORD CODE IN TABLE      @E@@@^          ER        ERR$YW
)@@G@@              . $A NO,EXIT YES      @G@@@^          ANX       X9,(1,1)  YX
)@@G@@        . $P X9 POINTS TO RECORD SEQUENCE @G@@@^          LA,H2     A3,0YY
)@@G@@,X9           . $P RECORD BUFFER ADDRESS TO A3  @G@@@^          JZ      YZ
)@@G@@  A3,UPDRET         . $T RECORD BUFFER INITIALIZED    @E@@@^            ZA
)@@G@@                          . $A NO,UPDRET YES    @G@@@^          LA      ZB
)@@G@@  A1,RDA+1          . $P DBP OF CHANGED RECORD TO A1  @E@@@^          TEZC
)@@G@@        A1,1,A3           . $T ARE DBPS EQUAL   @E@@@^          J       ZD
)@@G@@  UPDRET            . $A NO,UPDRET YES    @]@@@^ .          @C@@@^ . RECZE
)@@G@@ORD IN RECORD BUFFER SAME AS THAT IN RDA  @A@@@^ . UPDATE RECORD BUFFER ZF
)@@G@@FROM RDA    @]@@@^ .          @]@@@^ .          @]@@@^ .          @C@A@^ZG
)@@G@@          P$RINT    (PF1 1,4,UPDATEMSG)         @C@@@A .        P$RINT  ZH
)@@G@@  (PF1 1,4,UPDATEMSG)         @G@@@^          LX,U      X8,RDA          ZI
)@@G@@  . $P ORIGINATING ADDR TO X8       @G@@@^          LX        X9,A3     ZJ
)@@G@@        . $P DESTINATION ADDR TO X9       @C@@@^          LA,H2     A0,RZK
)@@G@@DA            .         @G@@@^          AA,U      A0,1              . $PZL
)@@G@@ LENGTH TO TRANSFER TO A0     @G@@@^          LR        R1,A0           ZM
)@@G@@  . $P LENGTH TO TRANSFER TO R1     @E@@@^          SLJ       RTRANS    ZN
)@@G@@        . $W RTRANS           @C@@@^UPDRET    J         *RBUFUPD        ZO
)@@G@@  . $E EXIT @A@@@^ . MAKE OWNER RECORD CURRENT OF SET @]@@@^ .          ZP
)@@G@@@]@@@^ .          @]@@@^OWNCUR .    @C@@@^          LX        X8,AENTAD ZQ
)@@G@@        .         @E@@@^          LA,T2     A1,0,X8           . SET CODEZR
)@@G@@ TO A1      @A@@@^          LX,H2     X9,TT2          @C@@@^          LXZS
)@@G@@I,U     X9,3              .         @C@@@^          LR,H1     R1,TT2    ZT
)@@G@@        .         @G@@@^          SE,T1     A1,,*X9           . $P SEARCZU
)@@G@@H SET CURRENCY TABLE    @^@@@^          ER        ERR$@G@@@^          ANZV
)@@G@@X       X9,(3,3)          . $P X9 POINTS TO SET CUR TBLE ENT@C@@@^      ZW
)@@G@@    LA        A1,IRCODE         .         @C@@@^          TE,T2     A1,0ZX
)@@G@@,X9           .         @^@@@^          ER        ERR$@G@@@^          SAZY
)@@G@@,T3     A1,0,X9           . $P UPDATE SET CURRENCY          @G@@@^      ZZ
)@@G@@    LA        A0,IRBFAD         . $P ADDR OF IR BUFFER TO A0      @C@@@^AA
)@@G@@          LA        A2,1,X9           . $       @I@@@^          SA      AB
)@@G@@  A2,2,X9           . $P DBP OF OLD CURRENT PUSHED DOWN           @C@@@^AC
)@@G@@          LA        A2,1,A0           . $       @G@@@^          SA      AD
)@@G@@  A2,1,X9           . $P NEW DBP TO TT2 TABLE         @E@@@^          J AE
)@@G@@        LNKEXT            . $J LNKEXT           @A@@@^SLMAN . ENTRY FOR AF
)@@G@@MANUAL SET        @I@@@^          SA        A0,MANLNKSW       . $P SET MAG
)@@G@@ANLNKSW TO IND MAN SET LINK         @E@@@^          J         LNGT11    AH
)@@G@@        . $J LNGT11           @]@@@^LNKEXT  .   @E@@@^          SZ      AI
)@@G@@  ISLNKSW           . $P ZERO ISLNKSW     @C@@@^          J         *SETAJ
)@@G@@LINK          . $E EXIT @]@@@^ .          @]@@@^ .          @]@@@^/     AK
)@@G@@      @C@@@^ . SUBROUTINE TO LOCATE ITEM SYM TAB ENTRY      @]@@@^ .    AL
)@@G@@      @C@@@^GETITEM   +         0              . $H GETITEM @G@@@^      AM
)@@G@@    LSSL      A1,18          . $T IS LINK WITHIN C15 OR C14       @E@@@^AN
)@@G@@          JN        A1,GETEM1      . $A NO,GETEM1 YES       @^@@@^ . ENTAO
)@@G@@RY IS WITHIN C15  @]@@@^ .          @G@@@^          SSL       A1,18     AP
)@@G@@     . $P REL LOCATION WITHIN C15 TO A1   @G@@@^          LA,H2     A0,CAQ
)@@G@@15         . $P ADDR OF C15 TBL TO A0           @G@@@^          LA,H1   AR
)@@G@@  A3,C15         . $P # OF WRDS IN C15 TO A3          @C@@@^          J AS
)@@G@@        GETEM2         . $J GETEM2  @]@@@^GETEM1 .    @A@@@^          LSAT
)@@G@@SL      A1,1           .@G@@@^          SSL       A1,19          . $P REAU
)@@G@@L LOC WITHIN C14 TO A1        @G@@@^          LA,H2     A0,C14         .AV
)@@G@@ $P ADDR OF C14 TBL TO A0           @G@@@^          LA,H1     A3,C14    AW
)@@G@@     . $P # OF WRDS IN C14 TO A3          @]@@@^GETEM2 .    @A@@@^      AX
)@@G@@    ANA,U     A3,3           .@G@@@^          TG        A1,A3          .AY
)@@G@@    RELATIVE POINTER WITHIN TABLE   @E@@@^          ER        ERR$      AZ
)@@G@@     .    INTERNAL ERROR      @E@@@^          AA        A0,A1          .BA
)@@G@@ $P POINT TO ITEM WANTED@C@@@^          J         *GETITEM       . $E EXBB
)@@G@@IT    @]@@@^ .          @]@@@^ .          @E@@@^TFUPDATE  +         0   BC
)@@G@@              . $H TFUPDATE         @]@@@^ .          @C@@@^ . SUBROUTINBD
)@@G@@E TO UPDATE THE TEMPORARY FILE      @E@@@^ . WILL INSERT THE CREATED RECBE
)@@G@@ORD IN THE TEMP FILE          @]@@@^ .          @G@@@^          SA      BF
)@@G@@  A0,IAPKT       . $P STORE IN FIRST WRD OF IAPKT H2  @G@@@^          LABG
)@@G@@,H2     A2,0,A1        . $P LENGTH OF RECORD TO A2          @G@@@^      BH
)@@G@@    SA,H2     A2,IAPKT+2     . $P LENGTH OF IR RECORD TO IAPKT    @^@@@^BI
)@@G@@          AA,U      A0,1@E@@@^          AA,U      A1,1           . $P ADBJ
)@@G@@DR OF RCD TO A1   @E@@@^          SA,H2     A1,IAPKT+1     . $P ADDR OF BK
)@@G@@RCD TO IAPKT@A@@@^          LX,U      X10,IAPKT      .@G@@@^          LMBL
)@@G@@J       X11,TF$IA      . $W TF$IA INSERT RECORD IN TEMP FILE@A@@@^      BM
)@@G@@    TZ,T1     IAPKT+2        .@E@@@^          ER        ERR$           .BN
)@@G@@  INTERNAL ERROR        @G@@@^          LA        A0,IAPKT          . $PBO
)@@G@@ UPDATE LINE NUMBER           @C@@@^          SA        A0,LN           BP
)@@G@@  .         @C@@@^          J         *TFUPDATE         . $P EXIT @]@@@^BQ
)@@G@@ .          @]@@@^ .          @]@@@^ .          @E@@@^ . SUBROUTINE TO EBR
)@@G@@STABLISH THE SET CURRENCY OF A GIVEN SET  @G@@@^ . UPON ENTRY:   SETCPKTBS
)@@G@@ PROPERLY CONTAINS DATAL SEE DESCRIPTION IN     @A@@@^ .                BT
)@@G@@  THE D BANK      @E@@@^ . UPON RETURN   SETCPKT CONTAINS SET CURRENCY IBU
)@@G@@NFORMATION  @]@@@^ .          @]@@@^ .          @]@@@^ .          @C@@@^BV
)@@G@@SETCUR .                           . $H SETCUR  @^@@@^          +       BW
)@@G@@  0   @E@@@^          LA,H2     A1,SETCPKT      . $P SET CODE TO A1     BX
)@@G@@@A@@@^ . SEARCH SET CURRENCY TABLE        @G@@@^          LX,H2     X9,TBY
)@@G@@T2         . $P SET CURRENCY TABLE ADDR         @G@@@^          LXI,U   BZ
)@@G@@  X9,3           . $P X9 WILL ICRREMENT BY 3          @E@@@^          LRCA
)@@G@@,H1     R1,TT2         . $P SET COUNT TO R1     @E@@@^          SE,T1   CB
)@@G@@  A1,,*X9        . $T FOUND SET ENTRY     @E@@@^          J         SCERCC
)@@G@@R1         . $A NO,SCERR1 YES       @E@@@^          ANX       X9,(3,3)  CD
)@@G@@     . $P BACK UP X9          @G@@@^          SX,H2     X9,SETCPKT+2   .CE
)@@G@@ $P SAVE PTR TO SET CUR TBLE        @G@@@^          LA,T3     A2,0,X9   CF
)@@G@@     . $P RECORD CODE OF CURRENT REC TO A2@^@@@^          TNZ       A2  CG
)@@G@@@A@@@^          J         SCERR2          @G@@@^          LSSL      A2,2CH
)@@G@@4          . $P GET RID OF EXTRA BITS           @A@@@^          SSL     CI
)@@G@@  A2,24           @G@@@^          SA,H2     A2,SETCPKT+1   . $P SAVE RCDCJ
)@@G@@ IN SETCPKT+1,,H2       @E@@@^          LA        A3,1,X9        . $P DBCK
)@@G@@P TO A3           @^@@@^ . SEARCH SEQUENCE TBL  @E@@@^          LR,H1   CL
)@@G@@  R1,TT1         . $P RCD SEQ COUNT TO R1 @G@@@^          LX,H2     X9,TCM
)@@G@@T1         . $P ADDR OF  SEQ TBL TO X9          @E@@@^          LXI,U   CN
)@@G@@  X9,1           . $P X9 TO INCREMENT BY 1@E@@@^          SE,T1     A2,,CO
)@@G@@*X9        . $T FOUND SET ENTRY     @E@@@^          J         SCERR3    CP
)@@G@@     . $A NO,SCERR3 YES       @G@@@^          ANX       X9,(1,1)       .CQ
)@@G@@ $P X9 POINTS TO REC ENTRY          @E@@@^          SX,H1     X9,SETCPKTCR
)@@G@@+2      . $P SAVE SEQ ENTRY   @G@@@^          LA,H2     A0,0,X9        .CS
)@@G@@ $P RCD BUFFER ADDR TO A0           @E@@@^          TNZ       A0        CT
)@@G@@     . $T PTR EXISTS          @E@@@^          J         SCERR4         .CU
)@@G@@ $A NO,SCERR4 YES       @A@@@^          SA,H1     A0,SETCPKT+1    @E@@@^CV
)@@G@@          SZ,H1     SETCPKT        . $P SET ZERO RETURN CODE@C@@@^SCEXT CW
)@@G@@    J         *SETCUR        . $E EXIT    @]@@@^ .          @]@@@^SCERR1CX
)@@G@@ .    @A@@@^          LA,U      A0,1           .@E@@@^          SA,H1   CY
)@@G@@  A0,SETCPKT        . $P SET RET CODE 1   @C@@@^          J         SCEXCZ
)@@G@@T          . $J SCEXT   @A@@@^SCERR2    LA,U      A0,2           .@E@@@^DA
)@@G@@          SA,H1     A0,SETCPKT        . $P SET RET CODE 2   @C@@@^      DB
)@@G@@    J         SCEXT          . $J SCEXT   @]@@@^SCERR3 .    @A@@@^      DC
)@@G@@    LA,U      A0,3           .@E@@@^          SA,H1     A0,SETCPKT      DD
)@@G@@  . $P SET RET CODE 3   @C@@@^          J         SCEXT          . $J SCDE
)@@G@@EXT   @]@@@^SCERR4 .    @A@@@^          LA,U      A0,4           .@E@@@^DF
)@@G@@          SA,H1     A0,SETCPKT        . $P SET RET CODE 4   @C@@@^      DG
)@@G@@    J         SCEXT          . $J SCEXT   @]@@@^.           @C@@@^ . ROUDH
)@@G@@TINE TO SEARCH A VARIABLE LENGTH TABLE.   @G@@@^ . UPON ENTRY  X10 POINTDI
)@@G@@S TO THE FIXED WORD IDENTIFYING THE TABLE.      @E@@@^ .                DJ
)@@G@@ THIS WORD HAS # OF WRDS IN TABLE IN H1   @G@@@^ .                      DK
)@@G@@         STARTING ADDRESS OF TABLE IN H2        @G@@@^ .             A1 DL
)@@G@@ CONTAINS SEARCH KEY WHICH IS T1 OF 1ST WORD OF ENTRY @E@@@^ . UPON RETUDM
)@@G@@RN A2  HAS RETURN CODE.  0= SUCCESSFUL          @E@@@^ .                DN
)@@G@@                   1= ENTRY NOT FOUND     @E@@@^ .                      DO
)@@G@@             2= TABLE EMPTY         @E@@@^ .             A0  WILL POINT DP
)@@G@@TO ENTRY FOUND IF ANY         @]@@@^ .          @]@@@^TABSE .     @C@@@^DQ
)@@G@@          +         0                 .         @E@@@^          TNZ,H1  DR
)@@G@@  0,X10     . $T ANY WORDS IN TABLE       @C@@@^          J         TABNDS
)@@G@@2     . $A NO,TABN2 YES @G@@@^          L,H2      A0,0,X10  . $P ADDRESSDT
)@@G@@ OF FIRST ENTRY TO A0         @E@@@^TALOP1    TNE,T1    A1,0,A0   . $T ADU
)@@G@@RE RECORD CODES EQUAL   @C@@@^          J         TABYES    . $A YES,TABDV
)@@G@@YES NO@E@@@^          TNZ,T3    0,A0      . $T IS THIS LAST ENTRY       DW
)@@G@@@C@@@^          J         TABN1     . $A YES,TABN1 NO @E@@@^          A,DX
)@@G@@T3      A0,0,A0   . $P POINT TO NEXT ENTRY      @A@@@^          J       DY
)@@G@@  TALOP1          @E@@@^TABN1     L,U       A2,1      . $P ITEM NOT FOUNDZ
)@@G@@D CODE      @C@@@^          J         TABEXT    . $J TABEXT       @C@@@^EA
)@@G@@TABN2     L,U       A2,2      . $P TABLE EMPTY  @C@@@^          J       EB
)@@G@@  TABEXT    . $J TABEXT       @G@@@^TABYES    L,U       A2,0      . $P SEC
)@@G@@ET SUCCESSFUL RETURN CODE           @C@@@^TABEXT    J         *TABSE    ED
)@@G@@ . $E EXIT        @]@@@^ .          @]@@@^ .          @C@@@^ . SUBROUTINEE
)@@G@@E TO CHANGE THE TEMPORARY FILE      @E@@@^ . . A0 HAS ADDRESS OF RECORD EF
)@@G@@BUFFER IN RDA FORMAT          @]@@@^ .          @C@@@^TFCHANGE  +       EG
)@@G@@  0                 . $H      @]@@@^ .          @]@@@^ .          @E@@@^EH
)@@G@@ . FIRST FIND THE RECORD CONCERNED IN THE TEMP FILE         @]@@@^ .    EI
)@@G@@      @]@@@^ .          @G@@@^          LA        A1,0,A0           . $PEJ
)@@G@@ FIRST WRD OF BUF TO CPKT     @G@@@^          SA,H2     A1,CPKT+2       EK
)@@G@@  . LENGTH OF RECORD TO CHANGE      @C@@@^          LA        A2,A0     EL
)@@G@@        .         @C@@@^          AA,U      A2,1              .         EM
)@@G@@@G@@@^          SA        A2,CPKT+1         . $P RECORD ADDRESS TO CPKT EN
)@@G@@      @E@@@^          LA        A1,1,A0   . $P DBP TO FIND TO A1        EO
)@@G@@@E@@@^          SA        A1,DBPPKT+1       . $P DBP TO PACKET    @C@@@^EP
)@@G@@          LX,U      X10,DBPPKT        .         @G@@@^          LMJ     EQ
)@@G@@  X11,TF$DBP1       . $W TF$DBP1 DONT DELIVER RECORD  @E@@@^          TZER
)@@G@@,T1     DBPPKT+2          . $T SUCCESSFUL       @C@@@^          ER      ES
)@@G@@  ERR$              .         @G@@@^          LA        A1,DBPPKT       ET
)@@G@@  . $P LINE NUMBER OF RECORD        @G@@@^          SA        A1,CPKT   EU
)@@G@@        . $P LINE NUMBER*[@@@@*SDFF*@]@@@@$(8)      . @B@@@@WC*       + EV
)@@G@@        2000               .  @B@@@@BUFFER*   RES       2000            EW
)@@G@@   .  @B@@@@WIDIT     INFO      2 8                .  @^@@@@          ENEX
)@@G@@D       .   ___@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@EY
)@@G@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@EZ
)@@G@@*[@@@@*SDFF*@I@@@#          AXR$.                                       FA
)@@G@@                  EBFD0001    @I@@@#. SUBROUTINE TO CONVERT EBCDIC TO FIFB
)@@G@@ELDATA                              EBFD0002    @I@@@#. FOR 360 TAPES.  FC
)@@G@@                                                      EBFD0003    @I@@@#FD
)@@G@@. CALL EBFD(IN,OUT,N)                                                   FE
)@@G@@EBFD0004    @I@@@#. IN IS ARRAY CONTAINING RECORD READ FROM 9 TRACK 8C9 FF
)@@G@@                  EBFD0005    @I@@@#. OUT IS ARRAY TO CONTAIN FIELDATA  FG
)@@G@@                                    EBFD0006    @I@@@#. N IS NUMBER OF BFH
)@@G@@YTES READ FROM TAPE                                   EBFD0007    @I@@@#FI
)@@G@@. N = (WORD COUNT - 1) / 2 * 9 + AFC                                    FJ
)@@G@@EBFD0008    @I@@@#$(1).                                                 FK
)@@G@@                  EBFD0009    @I@@@#EBFD*     S         R1,SR           FL
)@@G@@  .                                 EBFD0010    @I@@@#          S       FM
)@@G@@  R2,SR+1           .                                 EBFD0011    @I@@@#FN
)@@G@@          S         X1,SR+2           .                                 FO
)@@G@@EBFD0012    @I@@@#          SZ        A3                . FOR INDIRECT CFP
)@@G@@HAINING           EBFD0013    @I@@@#          L,U       A0,*0,X11       FQ
)@@G@@   . ADDRESS IN EBCDIC ARRAY        EBFD0014    @I@@@#          L,U     FR
)@@G@@  A1,*1,X11          . ADDRESS TO PUT FIELDATA        EBFD0015    @I@@@#FS
)@@G@@          LXI,U     A0,2              . INPUT BY PAIRS                  FT
)@@G@@EBFD0016    @I@@@#          LXI,U     A1,1              .               FU
)@@G@@                  EBFD0017    @I@@@#          L         R1,*2,X11       FV
)@@G@@  . N BYTES                         EBFD0018    @I@@@#          JGD     FW
)@@G@@  R1,$+1            .                                 EBFD0019    @I@@@#FX
)@@G@@          L,U       X1,STORE          . INITIAL STORE ADDRESS           FY
)@@G@@EBFD0020    @I@@@#LOAD      DL        A3,0,*A0          . GET 2 WORDS - FZ
)@@G@@9 BYTES           EBFD0021    @I@@@#          L,U       R2,8            GA
)@@G@@  . PROCESS 9 BYTES                 EBFD0022    @I@@@#ZERO      SZ      GB
)@@G@@  A2                .                                 EBFD0023    @I@@@#GC
)@@G@@          LDSL      A2,8              . GET 1 BYTE IIN LO-ORDER         GD
)@@G@@EBFD0024    @I@@@#          L,S6      A2,EFTAB,A2       . USE AS INDEX IGE
)@@G@@NTO TABLE         EBFD0025    @I@@@#          LMJ       X1,0,X1         GF
)@@G@@  . GO TO PROPER STORE INST         EBFD0026    @I@@@#BACK      JGD     GG
)@@G@@  R1,RESET          .                                 EBFD0027    @I@@@#GH
)@@G@@.         DONE !                                                        GI
)@@G@@EBFD0028    @I@@@#          L         R1,SR             .               GJ
)@@G@@                  EBFD0029    @I@@@#          L         R2,SR+1         GK
)@@G@@  .                                 EBFD0030    @I@@@#          L       GL
)@@G@@  X1,SR+2           .                                 EBFD0031    @I@@@#GM
)@@G@@          J         4,X11             . RETURN                          GN
)@@G@@EBFD0032    @I@@@#.                                                     GO
)@@G@@                  EBFD0033    @I@@@#RESET     DSL       A2,8            GP
)@@G@@  .                                 EBFD0034    @I@@@#          LDSL    GQ
)@@G@@  A3,8              .                                 EBFD0035    @I@@@#GR
)@@G@@          JGD       R2,ZERO                                             GS
)@@G@@EBFD0036    @I@@@#          J         LOAD              .               GT
)@@G@@                  EBFD0037    @I@@@#.                                   GU
)@@G@@                                    EBFD0038    @I@@@#JJ        LMJ     GV
)@@G@@  X1,0,X1           . RESET X1 TO LOC (TABLE)         EBFD0039    @I@@@#GW
)@@G@@STORE     S,S1      A2,0,A1           .                                 GX
)@@G@@EBFD0040    @I@@@#          LMJ       X1,0,X1           .               GY
)@@G@@                  EBFD0041    @I@@@#          S,S2      A2,0,A1         GZ
)@@G@@  .                                 EBFD0042    @I@@@#          LMJ     HA
)@@G@@  X1,0,X1           .                                 EBFD0043    @I@@@#HB
)@@G@@          S,S3      A2,0,A1           .                                 HC
)@@G@@EBFD0044    @I@@@#          LMJ       X1,0,X1           .               HD
)@@G@@                  EBFD0045    @I@@@#          S,S4      A2,0,A1         HE
)@@G@@  .                                 EBFD0046    @I@@@#          LMJ     HF
)@@G@@  X1,0,X1           .                                 EBFD0047    @I@@@#HG
)@@G@@          S,S5      A2,0,A1           .                                 HH
)@@G@@EBFD0048    @I@@@#          LMJ       X1,0,X1           .               HI
)@@G@@                  EBFD0049    @I@@@#          S,S6      A2,0,*A1        HJ
)@@G@@  . UP OUTPUT ADDRESS               EBFD0050    @I@@@#          J       HK
)@@G@@  JJ              .                                   EBFD0051    @I@@@#HL
)@@G@@.                                                                       HM
)@@G@@EBFD0052    @I@B@#$(0)                                                  HN
)@@G@@                  EBFD0053    @I@@@B$(0).                               HO
)@@G@@                                     EBFD005    @I@@@#SR        RES     HP
)@@G@@  3                 . SAVE AREA                       EBFD0054    @I@^@#HQ
)@@G@@EF*     PROC                                                            HR

)@@G@@EBFD0099    @I@@@#        EF      227     'T' .                         KA
)@@G@@                  EBFD0100    @I@@@#        EF      228     'U' .       KB
)@@G@@                                    EBFD0101    @I@@@#        EF      22KC
)@@G@@9     'V' .                                           EBFD0102    @I@@@#KD
)@@G@@        EF      230     'W' .                                           KE
)@@G@@EBFD0103    @I@@@#        EF      231     'X' .                         KF
)@@G@@                  EBFD0104    @I@@@#        EF      232     'Y' .       KG
)@@G@@                                    EBFD0105    @I@@@#        EF      23KH
)@@G@@3     'Z' .                                           EBFD0106    @I@@@#KI
)@@G@@        EF      240     '0' .                                           KJ
)@@G@@EBFD0107    @I@@@#        EF      241     '1' .                         KK
)@@G@@                  EBFD0108    @I@@@#        EF      242     '2' .       KL
)@@G@@                                    EBFD0109    @I@@@#        EF      24KM
)@@G@@3     '3' .                                           EBFD0110    @I@@@#KN
)@@G@@        EF      244     '4' .                                           KO
)@@G@@EBFD0111    @I@@@#        EF      245     '5' .                         KP

)@@G@@                                    EBFD0113    @I@@@#        EF      24KR

)@@G@@        EF      248     '8' .                                           KT
)@@G@@EBFD0115    @I@@@#        EF      249     '9' .                         KU
)@@G@@                  EBFD0116    @I@@@#        EF      255     '_' .       KV
)@@G@@                                    EBFD0117    @I@@@#        END       KW
)@@G@@                    .                                 EBFD0118    ___   KX
)@@G@@*[@@@@*SDFF*@B@@@@          AXR$                        .   @B@@@@$(1)  KY
)@@G@@    LIT                         .   @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @E@@@@.  FUNKZ
)@@G@@CTION TO TEST PRESENCE OF OPTION LETTERS OF @XQT CARD @[@@@@.     @ @@@@LA
)@@G@@.    IN FORTRAN, ONE CODES:   @[@@@@.     @^@@@@.    LOGICAL OPT,VARIAB LB
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @^@@@@.    VARIAB = OPT('C')  @[@@@@.     @F@@@@.     (FOR ELC
)@@G@@XAMPLE).  'VARIAB' WILL BE SET TO .TRUE. IF THERE IS  @F@@@@.     A 'C' LD
)@@G@@OPTION ON THE @XQT CARD (I.E. @XQT,C ), AND WILL BE   @A@@@@.     SET FALE
)@@G@@LSE IF THERE IS NOT.    @[@@@@.     @G@@@@. . . . . . . . . . . . . . . LF
)@@G@@. . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . @[@@@@.     @[@@@@$(2). @B@@@@LG
)@@G@@WUNCE     +         1                 .   @B@@@@OPTIONS   RES       1   LH
)@@G@@              .   @[@@@@$(1). @B@@@@OPT*      TNZ       WUNCE           LI
)@@G@@  .   @G@@@@          J         DID               . IF WE ALREADY HAVE OLJ
)@@G@@PT WRD.     @D@@@@          SZ        WUNCE             . CLEAR FLAG    LK
)@@G@@@F@@@@          ER        OPT$              . THEN DON'T REPEAT THINGS  LL
)@@G@@@D@@@@          SA        A0,OPTIONS        . GET AND SAVE  @E@@@@DID   LM
)@@G@@    LA        A0,OPTIONS        . GET THE OPTIONS WORD@E@@@@          L,LN
)@@G@@U       A1,'Z'            . PREPARE TO EXTRACT  @B@@@[          SZ      LO
)@@G@@  A3                .   @F@@@@          AN,S1     A1,*0,X11         . SULP
)@@G@@BTRACT CALLING LETTER   @D@@@@          SSL       A0,,A1            . . LQ
)@@G@@AND SHIFT   @B@@@@          J         2,X11             .   @#@@@@      LR
)@@G@@    END     ___@C1*?CK@^/K@@E(=9K[@@/K@@C1*WCK@I/K@@E7>9K]@@/K@@C1*WCK@ LS
)@@G@@*[@@@@*SDFF*@I@@@ .         CALL DUMPH(BUFFER,NBYTES) TO PRINT NBYTES RELT
)@@G@@AD FROM 9-TRACK   DUMPH001    @I@@@ .         TAPE IN BUFFER IN HEX FORMLU
)@@G@@AT                                  DUMPH002    @I@@@ .                 LV
)@@G@@                                                      DUMPH003    @I@@@ LW
)@@G@@$(0)      AXR$      .                                                   LX
)@@G@@DUMPH004    @I@@@ XS        RES       4                 .SAVE AREA      LY
)@@G@@                  DUMPH005    @I@@@ PB        RES       22              LZ
)@@G@@  . PRINT BUFFER                    DUMPH006    @I@@@ .                 MA
)@@G@@                                                      DUMPH007    @I@A@ MB
)@@G@@HEX       +         '0'               .                                 MC
)@@G@@DUMPH008    @I@A@           +         '1'               .               MD
)@@G@@                  DUMPH009    @I@A@           +         '2'             ME
)@@G@@  .                                 DUMPH010    @I@A@           +       MF
)@@G@@  '3'               .                                 DUMPH011    @I@A@ MG
)@@G@@          +         '4'               .                                 MH
)@@G@@DUMPH012    @I@A@           +         '5'               .               MI
)@@G@@                  DUMPH013    @I@A@           +         '6'             MJ
)@@G@@  .                                 DUMPH014    @I@A@           +       MK
)@@G@@  '7'               .                                 DUMPH015    @I@A@ ML
)@@G@@          +         '8'               .                                 MM
)@@G@@DUMPH016    @I@A@           +         '9'               .               MN
)@@G@@                  DUMPH017    @I@A@           +         'A'             MO
)@@G@@  .                                 DUMPH018    @I@A@           +       MP
)@@G@@  'B'               .                                 DUMPH019    @I@A@ MQ
)@@G@@          +         'C'               .                                 MR
)@@G@@DUMPH020    @I@A@           +         'D'               .               MS
)@@G@@                  DUMPH021    @I@A@           +         'E'             MT
)@@G@@  .                                 DUMPH022    @I@A@           +       MU
)@@G@@  'F'               .                                 DUMPH023    @I@@@ MV
)@@G@@.                                                                       MW
)@@G@@DUMPH024    @I@@@ /$(1).                                                MX
)@@G@@                  DUMPH025    @I@@@ DUMPH*    S         X11,XS          MY
)@@G@@  .                                 DUMPH026    @I@@@           S       MZ
)@@G@@  X1,XS+1           .                                 DUMPH027    @I@@@ NA
)@@G@@          S         X2,XS+2           .                                 NB
)@@G@@DUMPH028    @I@@@           S         X3,XS+3           .               NC
)@@G@@                  DUMPH029    @I@@@           SZ        A3              ND
)@@G@@  . CLEAR INDIRECT CHAINING         DUMPH030    @I@A@           L       NE
)@@G@@  R1,*1,X11         . # OF BYTES                      DUMPH031    @I@@@ANF
)@@G@@          L         A1,*1,X11         . # OF BYTES                      NG
)@@G@@DUMPH031    @F@@@A          LSSL      A1,1              . *2 FOR # OF HENH
)@@G@@X CHARS     @B@@@A          L         R1,A1             .   @I@@@       NI
)@@G@@    JGD       R1,$+1            .                                 DUMPH0NJ
)@@G@@32    @I@@@           L,U       X1,*0,X11         . ADDRESS OF BUFFER   NK
)@@G@@            DUMPH033    @I@@@           LXI,U     X1,2              . INNL
)@@G@@PUT IN PAIRS                  DUMPH034    @I@@@           L         X2,(NM
)@@G@@-1,5)         . INSTRUCTION CHASER              DUMPH035    @I@@@       NN
)@@G@@    L         X3,(1,PB)         . CHARACTER POINTER               DUMPH0NO
)@@G@@36    @I@@@           LMJ       X11,BLANK         . BLANK OUT PRINT BUFFNP
)@@G@@ER          DUMPH037    @I@@@           L,U       R2,131            . 13NQ
)@@G@@2 CHARACTERS IN PB            DUMPH038    @I@A@ RL01      L,U       R3,8NR
)@@G@@              . 9 BYTES PER DOUBLE WORD         DUMPH039    @I@@@ARL01  NS
)@@G@@    L,U       R3,17              . 18 HEX CHARS PER DOUBLE WORD         NT
)@@G@@DU    @I@@@           DL        A1,0,*X1          . GET 2 WORDS - 9 BYTENU
)@@G@@S           DUMPH040    @I@@@ RL02      SZ        A0                . CLNV
)@@G@@EAR COLLECTION AREA           DUMPH041    @I@@@           LDSL      A0,4NW
)@@G@@              . GET 4 BITS                      DUMPH042    @I@B@       NX
)@@G@@    L,S6      A0,HEX,A0         . USE AS INDEX INTO HEX TABLE     DUMPH0NY
)@@G@@43    @E@@@A          A,U       A0,'0'            . MAKE IT A NUMBER    NZ
)@@G@@@E@@@A          TG,U      A0,'9'+1          . IF > 9, THEN A-F    @D@D@AOA
)@@G@@          A,U       A0,'A'-'0'-10     . MAKE IT A-F   @D@@@D          A,OB
)@@G@@U       A0,'A'-'0'-9      . MAKE IT A-F   @I@@@           EX        STO,OC
)@@G@@X2            . PLACE IN PB                     DUMPH044    @]@C@AMAIN/TOD
)@@G@@DUMP  @ @C@ADUMPH/TDUMP,BUFFERS/TDUMP     @#@C@ASETUP/TDUMP,XREAD @]@C@AOE
)@@G@@EBFD/TDUMP  @D@C@AWIDIT . PUT COMMON BLOCK AT TOP OF DBANKE FOR MCORE$  OF
)@@G@@@I@@@           JMGI      X2,$+2            .                           OG
)@@G@@      DUMPH045    @I@@@           L         X2,(-1,5)         .         OH
)@@G@@                        DUMPH046    @I@@@           SSL       A1,4      OI
)@@G@@        . RESTORE A1                      DUMPH047    @I@@@           LDOJ
)@@G@@SL      A1,4              . MOVE OVER NEXT 4 BITS           DUMPH048    OK
)@@G@@@I@@@           JGD       R1,$+2            .                           OL
)@@G@@      DUMPH049    @I@@@           J         ALLDONE           .         OM
)@@G@@                        DUMPH050    @I@@@           JGD       R2,NOTFULLON
)@@G@@        .                                 DUMPH051    @I@@@           P$OO
)@@G@@RINT    (0126,PB)                                           DUMPH052    OP
)@@G@@@I@@@           LMJ       X11,BLANK         .                           OQ
)@@G@@      DUMPH053    @I@@@           L         X3,(1,PB)                   OR
)@@G@@                        DUMPH054    @I@@@           L,U       R2,131    OS
)@@G@@                                          DUMPH055    @I@@@ NOTFULL   JGOT
)@@G@@D       R3,RL02                                             DUMPH056    OU
)@@G@@@I@@@           J         RL01              .                           OV
)@@G@@      DUMPH057    @I@@@ .                                               OW
)@@G@@                        DUMPH058    @I@@@ ALLDONE   P$RINT    (0126,PB) OX
)@@G@@                                          DUMPH059    @I@@@           L OY
)@@G@@        X11,XS.                                             DUMPH060    OZ
)@@G@@@I@@@           L         X1,XS+1           .                           PA
)@@G@@      DUMPH061    @I@@@           L         X2,XS+2           .         PB
)@@G@@                        DUMPH062    @I@@@           L         X3,XS+3   PC
)@@G@@        .                                 DUMPH063    @I@@@           J PD
)@@G@@        3,X11             . RETURN TO CALLER                DUMPH064    PE
)@@G@@@I@@@ .                                                                 PF
)@@G@@      DUMPH065    @I@A@ BLANK     L         A0,('      ')               PG
)@@G@@                        00000066    @I@@@ABLANK     L         A0,('     PH
)@@G@@ ')     .                                 DUMPH066    @I@A@           L PI
)@@G@@        A3,(-1,PB+21)                                       00000067    PJ
)@@G@@@I@@@A          L         A3,(-1,21)                                    PK
)@@G@@   000DUMPH067    @I@A@           S         A0,0,A3                     PL
)@@G@@                        00000068    @I@@@A          S         A0,PB,A3 .PM
)@@G@@                                          DUMPH068    @I@@@           JMPN
)@@G@@GI      A3,$-1            .                                 DUMPH069    PO
)@@G@@@I@@@           J         0,X11             .                           PP
)@@G@@      DUMPH070    @I@@@ .                                               PQ
)@@G@@                        DUMPH071    @I@@@ .                             PR
)@@G@@                                          DUMPH072    @I@@@ STO       S,PS
)@@G@@S6      A0,,*X3           .                                 DUMPH073    PT
)@@G@@@I@@@           S,S5      A0,,X3            .                           PU
)@@G@@      DUMPH074    @I@@@           S,S4      A0,,X3            .         PV
)@@G@@                        DUMPH075    @I@@@           S,S3      A0,,X3    PW
)@@G@@        .                                 DUMPH076    @I@@@           S,PX
)@@G@@S2      A0,,X3            .                                 DUMPH077    PY
)@@G@@@I@@@           S,S1      A0,,X3            .                           PZ
)@@G@@      DUMPH078    @I@@@ .                                               QA
)@@G@@                        DUMPH079    @I@A@           END                 QB
)@@G@@                                          00000080    @I@@@A          ENQC
)@@G@@D                         .                                 DUMPH080    QD
)@@G@@___ LSSL      A1,1              . *2 FOR # OF HEX CHARS     @B@@@A      QE
)@@G@@    L         R1,A1             .   @I@@@       *[@@@@*SDFF*@^@@@@A0$*  QF
)@@G@@    RES       1   @^@@@@A1$*      RES       1   @^@@@@A2$*      RES     QG
)@@G@@  1   @^@@@@A3$*      RES       1   @^@@@@A4$*      RES       1   @^@@@@QH
)@@G@@A5$*      RES       1   @^@@@@X11$*     RES       1   @^@@@@R1$*      REQI
)@@G@@S       1   @^@@@@R2$*      RES       1   @^@@@@R3$*      RES       1   QJ
)@@G@@@#@@@@          END     ___@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@QK
)@@G@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@QL
)@@G@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@*[S@@@*SDFF*@[@@@AC     QM
)@@G@@@^@@@AC    BY K. E. SIBBALD   @[@@@AC     @ @@@^      SUBROUTINE DUMPA(BQN
)@@G@@UF,NW)@ @@@^      DIMENSION BUF(2000)     @B@C@^      COMMON /EDIT/EDPKTQO
)@@G@@(6),IMAGE(22)     @B@@@C      COMMON /EDIT/EDPKT(10),IMAGE(22)    @^@@@ QP
)@@G@@      LOGICAL BATCH     @C@@@^      N=0                             @ COQQ
)@@G@@UNTER @E@@@^      NWL=NW                          @ NO. OF WORDS LEFT   QR
)@@G@@@F@@@       NWPL=9                          @ NUMBER OF WORDS PER LINE  QS
)@@G@@@G@B@       IF(BATCH(1)) NWPL=1             @ MORE WORDS PER LINE IN BATQT
)@@G@@CH    @G@@@B      IF(BATCH(1)) NWPL=16            @ MORE WORDS PER LINE QU
)@@G@@IN BATCH    @G@@@       CALL SKIP(1)                    @ SKIP A LINE BEQV
)@@G@@FORE PRINTING     @D@ @^10    IF(NWL.LT.9) GOTO 30            @ DO LAST QW
)@@G@@BIT   @D@@@ 10    IF(NWL.LT.NWPL) GOTO 30         @ DO LAST LINE  @A@@@^QX
)@@G@@      CALL EOPEN(EDPKT,22,IMAGE)    @#@ @^      DO 20 I=1,9 @^@@@       QY
)@@G@@DO 20 I=1,NWPL    @]@@@^      N=N+1 @C@@@^      CALL ESKIP(EDPKT,2)     QZ
)@@G@@        @ SPACE 2 @A@@@^      CALL ECOPY(EDPKT,6,BUF(N))    @#@@@^20    RA
)@@G@@CONTINUE    @D@@@^      CALL EPRINT(EDPKT,1)            @ PRINT ONE LINERB
)@@G@@@F@ @^      NWL=NWL-9                       @ DECREMENT NO. WORDS LEFT  RC
)@@G@@@F@@@       NWL=NWL-NWPL                    @ DECREMENT NO. WORDS LEFT  RD
)@@G@@@#@@@^      GOTO 10     @A@ @^30    CALL EOPEN(EDPKT,22,IMAGE)    @G@@@ RE
)@@G@@30    IF(NWL.EQ.0) RETURN             @ RETURN IF NOTHING MORE TO PRINT RF
)@@G@@@A@@@       CALL EOPEN(EDPKT,22,IMAGE)    @^@@@^      DO 40 I=1,NWL     RG
)@@G@@@]@@@^      N=N+1 @C@@@^      CALL ESKIP(EDPKT,2)             @ SPACE 2 RH
)@@G@@@A@@@^      CALL ECOPY(EDPKT,6,BUF(N))    @#@@@^40    CONTINUE    @E@@@^RI
)@@G@@      CALL EPRINT(EDPKT,1)            @ PRINT LAST LINE     @]@@@^      RJ
)@@G@@RETURN@]@@@^      END   ___@@@      S(K3,L2) = S(K3,L2) + C2*WV + C3*VW RK
)@@G@@                                          @I@@@@                        RL
)@@G@@                        *[S@@@*SDFF*@[@@@AC     @^@@@AC   BY KERN E. SIBRM
)@@G@@BALD  @[@@@AC     @ @^@#      SUBROUTINE DUMPA(BUF,NW)@ @@@^      SUBROURN
)@@G@@TINE DUMPO(BUF,NW)@ @@@#      DIMENSION BUF(2000)     @B@B@#      COMMONRO
)@@G@@ /EDIT/EDPKT(6),IMAGE(22)     @B@@@B      COMMON /EDIT/EDPKT(10),IMAGE(2RP
)@@G@@2)    @^@@@       LOGICAL BATCH     @C@@@#      N=0                     RQ
)@@G@@        @ COUNTER @E@@@#      NWL=NW                          @ NO. OF WRR
)@@G@@ORDS LEFT   @F@@@^      NWPL=5                          @ NUMBER OF WORDRS
)@@G@@S PER LINE  @F@@@       IF(BATCH(1)) NWPL=9             @ MORE WORDS ON RT
)@@G@@BATCH LINE  @G@@@       CALL SKIP(1)                    @ SKIP A LINE BERU
)@@G@@FORE PRINTING     @D@^@#10    IF(NWL.LT.5) GOTO 30            @ DO LAST RV
)@@G@@BIT   @C@@@^10    IF(NWL.LT.NWPL) GOTO 30 @ DO LAST LINE    @A@@@#      RW
)@@G@@CALL EOPEN(EDPKT,22,IMAGE)    @#@^@#      DO 20 I=1,5 @^@@@^      DO 20 RX
)@@G@@I=1,NWPL    @C@@@#      CALL ESKIP(EDPKT,2)             @ SPACE 2 @]@@@#RY
)@@G@@      N=N+1 @A@@@#      CALL EOCTF(EDPKT,12,BUF(N))   @#@@@#20    CONTINRZ
)@@G@@UE    @D@@@#      CALL EPRINT(EDPKT,1)            @ PRINT ONE LINE@F@^@#SA
)@@G@@      NWL=NWL-5                       @ DECREMENT NO. WORDS LEFT  @F@@@^SB
)@@G@@      NWL=NWL-NWPL                    @ DECREMENT NO. WORDS LEFT  @#@@@#SC
)@@G@@      GOTO 10     @A@ @#30    CALL EOPEN(EDPKT,22,IMAGE)    @F@@@ 30    SD
)@@G@@IF (NWL.EQ.0) RETURN            @ RETURN IF NOTHING MORE    @A@@@       SE
)@@G@@CALL EOPEN(EDPKT,22,IMAGE)    @^@@@#      DO 40 I=1,NWL     @]@@@#      SF
)@@G@@N=N+1 @C@@@#      CALL ESKIP(EDPKT,2)             @ SPACE 2 @A@@@#      SG
)@@G@@CALL EOCTF(EDPKT,12,BUF(N))   @#@@@#40    CONTINUE    @E@@@#      CALL ESH
)@@G@@PRINT(EDPKT,1)            @ PRINT LAST LINE     @]@@@#      RETURN@]@@@#SI
)@@G@@      END   ___         @I@@@@      DO 405 L=1,N*[S@@@*SDFF*@^@@@@      SJ
)@@G@@SUBROUTINE RWB    @[@@@@C     @F@@@@C *** THIS ONE PRINTS THE TALLY OF RSK
)@@G@@ECORDS WITH THE SAME NO. OF   @#@@@@C *** WORDS READ  @[@@@@C     @A@@@@SL
)@@G@@      COMMON NEOFS,NREC,NWB,NRECB   @B@#@[      COMMON /EDIT/ EDPKT(6),ISM
)@@G@@MAGE(22)    @B@@@#      COMMON /EDIT/ EDPKT(10),IMAGE(22)   @ @@@@      SN
)@@G@@IF(NRECB.EQ.0) GOTO 180 @ @[@@      PRINT 160,NRECB,NWB     @C@[@@160   SO
)@@G@@FORMAT(I7,' RECORDS OF ',I6,' WORDS')     @A@]@[      CALL EOPEN(EDPKT,ISP
)@@G@@MAGE,22)    @A@@@]      CALL EOPEN(EDPKT,22,IMAGE)    @C@@@[      CALL ESQ
)@@G@@DECF(EDPKT,7,NRECB) @ NO. OF RECORDS@C@@@[      CALL EMSG(EDPKT,' RECORDSR
)@@G@@S OF & WORDS&')   @ @@@[      CALL EDECF(EDPKT,6,NWB) @^@@@[      CALL ESS
)@@G@@MSGR(EDPKT) @B@@@[      CALL EPRINT(EDPKT,1) @ PRINT IT     @G@@@@180   ST
)@@G@@NRECB=0                          @ ZERO NO. REC. OF SAME NO. WRDS.@G@@@@SU
)@@G@@      NWB=0                            @ ZERO NO WORDS IN THOSE RECORDS SV
)@@G@@@]@@@@      RETURN@]@@@@      END   ___OT.OPT('C')) GO TO 812     @B@@@^SW
)@@G@@          IF(.NOT.OPT('Y')) GO TO 812     @ @@@]*[S@@@*SDFF*@^@@@@      SX
)@@G@@SUBROUTINE FILREC @[@@@@C     @E@@@@C *** THIS SUBROUTINE PRINTS THE FILSY
)@@G@@E AND THE RECORD COUNT  @[@@@@C     @A@@@@      COMMON NEOFS,NREC,NWB,NRSZ
)@@G@@ECB   @B@#@[      COMMON /EDIT/ EDPKT(6),LINE(22)     @B@@@#      COMMONTA
)@@G@@ /EDIT/ EDPKT(10),LINE(22)    @ @[@@      PRINT 100,NEOFS,NREC    @B@[@@TB
)@@G@@100   FORMAT(' FILE ',I5,5X,'RECORD ',I6) @A@]@[      CALL EOPEN(EDPKT,LTC
)@@G@@INE,22)     @A@@@]      CALL EOPEN(EDPKT,22,LINE)     @C@@@[      CALL ETD
)@@G@@MSG(EDPKT,' FILE &     RECORD &')   @A@@@[      CALL EDECF(EDPKT,5,NEOFSTE
)@@G@@)     @^@@@[      CALL EMSGR(EDPKT) @ @@@[      CALL EDECF(EDPKT,6,NREC)TF
)@@G@@@E@@@[      CALL EPRINT(EDPKT,1)            @ PRINT THE MESSAGE   @]@@@@TG
)@@G@@      RETURN@]@@@@      END   ___(S(IT).EQ.0).OR.(S(IT).EQ.1)) GOTO 140 TH
)@@G@@@C@@@[110   IF(OPT('O')) CALL DUMPO(BUF(1,IT),NW(IT)) @C@@@[      IF(OPTTI
)@@G@@('A')) CALL DUMPA(BUF(1,*[S@@@*SDFF*@#@@@D          AXR$    @[@@@D$(1)  TJ
)@@G@@@]@@@DDUMPH* .    @ @@@D. DUMP HEXADECIMAL FORMAT     @A@@@D          L TK
)@@G@@        A0,(0100,BUF)   @ @@@D          ER        PRINT$    @^@@@D      TL
)@@G@@    SZ        A3  @ @@@D          L         R3,*1,X11 @ @@@D          S TM
)@@G@@        X1,SAVX1  @ @@@D          S         X2,SAVX2  @ @@@D          S TN
)@@G@@        X3,SAVX3  @ @@@D          L,U       X3,*0,X11 @^@@@D          LXTO
)@@G@@I,U     X3,1@[@@@DPER   @ @@@D          L         X1,(1,BUF)@A@@@D      TP
)@@G@@    L         X2,(1,STOR)     @ @@@D          L,U       A4,' '    @ @@@DTQ
)@@G@@          EX        0,*X2     @ @@@D          EX        0,*X2     @ @@@DTR
)@@G@@          L,U       R2,12     @[@@@DREP   @ @@@D          JGD       R3,$TS
)@@G@@+2    @^@@@D          J         EXIT@ @@@D          L         A1,0,*X3  TT
)@@G@@@^@@@D          L,U       R1,8@[@@@DRPE   @^@@@D          LSSC      A1,4TU
)@@G@@@ @@@D          AND,U     A1,017    @A@@@D          L         A4,BINHEX,TV
)@@G@@A2    @ @@@D          EX        0,*X2     @ @@@D          JGD       R1,RTW
)@@G@@PE    @ @@@D          L,U       A4,' '    @ @@@D          EX        0,*XTX
)@@G@@2     @ @@@D          JGD       R2,REP    @ @@@D          L,U       A0,0TY
)@@G@@,X1   @ @@@D          AN,U      A0,BUF    @ @@@D          LSSL      A0,1TZ
)@@G@@8     @A@@@D          A         A0,(0100,BUF)   @ @@@D          ER      UA
)@@G@@  PRINT$    @^@@@D          J         PER @[@@@DEXIT  @ @@@D          L,UB
)@@G@@U       A4,' '    @ @@@D          EX        0,*X2     @ @@@D          EXUC
)@@G@@        0,*X2     @ @@@D          EX        0,*X2     @ @@@D          EXUD

)@@G@@*[S@@@*SDFF*@B@@@@          AXR$                        .   @B@[@@$(1)  YD
)@@G@@                                .   @B@@@[$(1)      LIT                 YE
)@@G@@        .   @F@@@[EDPKT     E$PKTF    0,$ SPC,'E' DPC,'D' . GENERATE EDIYF
)@@G@@T$ PACKET   @F@@@[PKTLEN    EQU       $-EDPKT           . LENGTH OF EDITYG
)@@G@@ PACKET     @B@@@@P         PROC                        .   @B@@@@LINK* YH
)@@G@@    NAME                        .   @B@@@@DLINK*    NAME      1         YI
)@@G@@        .   @D@@@@          LMJ       A1,EDITRF         . REOPEN EDIT   YJ
)@@G@@@B@@@@          UNLIST                      .   @D@@@@          ON      YK
)@@G@@  P(0,0)>0          . GET ARGUMENTS @B@@@@          DL        A0,*1,X11 YL
)@@G@@        .   @B@@@@          OFF                         .   @B@@@@      YM
)@@G@@    ON        P(0,0)=0          .   @B@@@@          DO        P(2,1)>0 ,YN

)@@G@@        .   @B@@@@          OFF                         .   @E@@@@      YQ

)@@G@@ P(3,1)>0 , L X11,A4      .   @B@@@@          DO P(3,1)>0 , S A0,*1,X11 YS
)@@G@@  .   @D@@@@          LMJ       A1,EDITXF         . CLOSE EDIT    @C@@@@YT
)@@G@@          J         P(2,1)+P(3,1)+2,X11 . RETURN@B@@@@          LIST    YU
)@@G@@                    .   @B@@@@          END                         .   YV
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @B@@@@EDITRF                                .   @D@@@@      YW
)@@G@@    S         X11,A4            . SAVE RETURN   @E@@@@          S       YX

)@@G@@              .   @F@@@@          L,U       A0,*0,X11         . GET ADDRYZ

)@@G@@        X11,A4            . RESTORE ANOTHER RETURN    @H@@@]          SZZC

)@@G@@          J         0,A1              .   @[@@@@.     @B@@@@EDITXF      ZE
)@@G@@                          .   @D@@@@          S         A1,A5           ZF

)@@G@@              .   @[@@@@.     @B@@@@.         CALL EOPEN(PKT,IMLEN,IMAGEZJ
)@@G@@)     @[@@@@.     @B@@@@EOPEN*                                .   @E@@@[ZK
)@@G@@          SZ        A3                . CLEAR FOR L,U AX,*  @D@[@@      ZL
)@@G@@    DSL       A2,72             . CLEAR A2,A3   @D@@@@          S       ZM
)@@G@@  X11,A4            . SAVE RETURN   @I@@@[          L,U       R1,PKTLEN ZN
)@@G@@        . SET TO TRANSFER DUMMY PACKET TO USER BUF    @F@@@[          L ZO
)@@G@@        A1,(1,EDPKT)      . ADDRESS OF DUMMY PACKET   @E@@@[          L,ZP

)@@G@@        . TRANSFER PACKET     @E@@@@          L,U       A0,*0,X11       ZS
)@@G@@  . ADDRESS OF PACKET   @D@[@@          DS        A2,0,A0           . CLZT
)@@G@@EAR PACKET  @B@[@@          DS        A2,2,A0           .   @B@[@@      ZU
)@@G@@    DS        A2,4,A0           .   @B@[@@          DS        A2,6,A0   ZV

)@@G@@@C@[@@          L,U       A1,'&'            . MSG CHAR@B@[@@          S,AA
)@@G@@S2      A1,0,A0           .   @F@[@@          L,U       A1,1            AB

)@@G@@@F@[@@          S,S2      A1,2,A0           . FLOATING POINT ROUNDING ONAE
)@@G@@@F@[@@          L,U       A1,'D'            . DOUBLE PRECISION SEPARATORAF

)@@G@@    LINK      ECOL$     1       .   @B@@@@ESKIP*    LINK      ESKIP$    AL

)@@G@@1       .   @B@@@@EDAY3*    LINK      EDAY3$    1       .   @[@@@@.     AW
)@@G@@@A@@@@.         CALL EPRINT(PKT,NSPACE)   @[@@@@.     @B@@@@EPRINT*     AX
)@@G@@                          .   @B@@@@          S         X11,A4          AY
)@@G@@  .   @B@@@@          SZ        A3                .   @F@@@@          L,AZ
)@@G@@U       A0,*0,X11         . ADDRESS OF EDIT PACKET    @D@@@@          E$BA
)@@G@@DITR                      . REOPEN EDIT   @E@@@@          E$COLN        BB
)@@G@@              . GET CHARACTER COUNT @E@@@@          S         A0,A5     BC
)@@G@@        . SAVE CHARACTER COUNT@A@@@@          E$DITX    .  CLOSE EDIT   BD
)@@G@@@E@@@@          L         A0,A5             . GET CHARACTER COUNT @E@@@@BE
)@@G@@          DSL       A0,36             . GET READY TO DIVIDE @F@@@@      BF
)@@G@@    DI,U      A0,6              . DIVIDE TO GET WORD COUNT  @F@@@@      BG
)@@G@@    TZ        A1                . IF THERE IS A REMAINDER,  @C@@@@      BH
)@@G@@    A,U       A0,1              .    ADD 1@G@@@@          TLE,U     A0,2BI
)@@G@@3             . IS IMAGE LONGER THAN 22 WORDS?  @E@@@@          J       BJ
)@@G@@  EPR000            . NO, GO PRINT IMAGE  @E@@@@          L         A0,EBK
)@@G@@PR020         . PRINT ERROR MESSAGE @B@@@@          ER        PRINT$    BL
)@@G@@        .   @G@@@@          L,U       A0,22             . SET IMAGE LENGBM
)@@G@@TH TO 22 WORDS    @B@@@@EPR000                                .   @D@@@@BN
)@@G@@          L         X11,A4            . RESTORE RETURN@B@@@@          SZBO
)@@G@@        A3                .   @E@@@@          LSSL      A0,30           BP
)@@G@@  . SHIFT WORD COUNT    @F@@@@          L,U       A2,*0,X11         . ADBQ
)@@G@@DRESS OF EDIT PACKET    @D@@@@          L         A1,*1,X11         . SKBR
)@@G@@IP COUNT    @G@@@@          DSC       A0,12             . ALLIGN SKIP COBS
)@@G@@UNT, WORD COUNT   @E@@@@          LXM       A0,0,A2,H2        . ADDRESS BT
)@@G@@OF IMAGE    @D@@@@          ER        PRINT$            . PRINT IMAGE   BU
)@@G@@@C@@@@          J         3,X11             . RETURN  @]@@@@EPR010    . BV
)@@G@@@G@@@@ '*** FOLLOWING IMAGE TRUNCATED TO 22 WORDS - SUBROUTINE EPRINT **BW
)@@G@@*'    @B@@@@EPR020    +0100+$-EPR010,EPR010       .   @B@@@@          ENBX
)@@G@@D                         .   ___@@@          L         X11,A4          BY
)@@G@@  . RESTORE ANOTHER RETU*[S@@@*SDFF*@[@@@F.     @D@@@F. THIS ROUTINE WRIBZ
)@@G@@TES TTHE SPECIFIED BUFFER TO THE    @#@@@F. OUTPUT TAPE     @ @@@F. THE CA
)@@G@@CALLING SEQUENCE IS     @[@@@F.     @^@@@F.         LMJ X11,OUT   @A@@@FCB
)@@G@@.         +BINARY OUTPUT UNIT NUMBER@^@@@F.         +BUFFER ADDRES@ @@@FCC
)@@G@@.         +NUMBER OF WORDS    @D@@@F.         +FUNCTION (IF 0 WEF$, IF 1CD
)@@G@@ W$, IF 2 REW$)   @ @@@F.         +WALK BACK WORD     @[@@@F.     @[@@@FCE
)@@G@@.     @D@@@F. AN ALTERNATE ENTRY TO WAIT FOR I/0 TO COMPLETE CALL @[@@@FCF
)@@G@@.     @#@@@F.   LMJ X11,OWAIT @]@@@F.  +STATUS  @^@@@F.   +WALK BACK WORCG
)@@G@@D     @[@@@F.     @[@@@F.     @D@@@FP         FORM      12,6,18         CH
)@@G@@  . PRINT FORM    @^@@@F$(1)      AXR$      .   @[@@@F.     @]@@@FMBACK*CI
)@@G@@.     @D@@@I          S         X11,SAVEX11       . FOR DEBUG     @D@@@FCJ
)@@G@@          TZ        NOUT              . ANY UNIT?     @D@@@F          J CK
)@@G@@        2,X11             . NO, RETURN    @D@@@F          TP        IOPKCL
)@@G@@T+3           . WAIT FOR I/O  @C@@@F          ER        WAIT$           CM
)@@G@@  . WAIT    @D@@@F          L,U       A1,MB$            . GET MOVE BACK CN
)@@G@@@E@@@F          S,T1      A1,FUNC           . SET THE FUNCTION    @E@@@FCO
)@@G@@          L,U       A0,IOPKT          . STORE IN PACKET     @D@@@F      CP
)@@G@@    ER        IO$               . MOVE BACK     @E@@@F          J       CQ
)@@G@@  2,X11             . RETURN TO CALLER    @]@@@FOWAIT*.     @D@@@I      CR
)@@G@@    S         X11,SAVEX11       . FOR DEBUG     @F@@@F          TZ      CS
)@@G@@  NOUT              . IS THERE AN OUTPUT TAPE?  @D@@@F          J       CT
)@@G@@  2,X11             . NO, RETURN    @D@@@F          TP        IOPKT+3   CU
)@@G@@        . WAIT FOR I/O  @B@@@F          ER        WAIT$             .   CV
)@@G@@@B@@@F          SZ        A3                .   @D@@@F          L,S1    CW
)@@G@@  A0,FUNC           . GET THE STATUS@F@@@F          S         A0,*0,X11 CX
)@@G@@        . RETURN STATUS TO CALLER   @C@@@F          J         2,X11     CY
)@@G@@        . RETURN  @[@@@F.     @[@@@F.     @[@@@FOUT*. @D@@@I          S CZ
)@@G@@        X11,SAVEX11       . FOR DEBUG     @F@@@F          TZ        NOUTDA
)@@G@@              . IS THERE AN OUTPUT TAPE?  @D@@@F          J         5,X1DB
)@@G@@1             . NO, RETURN    @E@@@F          TP        IOPKT+3         DC
)@@G@@  . IS I/O IN PROGRESS? @C@@@F          ER        WAIT$             . YEDD
)@@G@@S WAIT@E@@@F          TNZ       IOPKT             . IS FILE ASSIGNED?   DE
)@@G@@@D@@@F          SLJ       ASG               . NO ASSIGN IT  @B@@@F      DF
)@@G@@    SZ        A3                .   @D@@@F          L         A0,*3,X11 DG
)@@G@@        . GET FUNCTION  @H@@@F          JNZ       A0,ZEROOK         . IFDH
)@@G@@ EOF OR REWIND, ZERO COUNT IS OK    @E@@@F          TNZ       *2,X11    DI
)@@G@@        . NON-ZERO WORD COUNT?@D@@@F          J         5,X11           DJ
)@@G@@  . NO, RETURN    @]@@@FZEROOK.     @E@@@F          L,U       A0,*1,X11 DK
)@@G@@        . GET BUFFER ADDRESS  @D@@@F          LXI       A0,*2,X11       DL
)@@G@@  . GET WORD COUNT@E@@@F          S         A0,ACWD           . STORE INDM
)@@G@@ I/O PACKET @F@@@F          L         A0,*3,X11         . GET REQUESTED DN
)@@G@@FUNCTION    @E@@@F          L,U       A1,W$             . GET WRITE FUNCDO
)@@G@@TION  @E@@@F          TNE,U     A0,1              . REQUEST FOR EOF?    DP
)@@G@@@F@@@F          L,U       A1,WEF$           . YES, GET EOF FUNCTION     DQ
)@@G@@@F@@@F          TNE,U     A0,2              . IS IT A REWIND REQUEST?   DR
)@@G@@@F@@@F          L,U       A1,REW$           . YES, GET REWIND FUNCTION  DS
)@@G@@@E@@@F          S,T1      A1,FUNC           . SET THE FUNCTION    @D@@@FDT
)@@G@@          L,U       A0,IOPKT          . PACKET ADDRESS@C@@@F          ERDU
)@@G@@        IO$               . WRITE   @C@@@F          J         5,X11     DV
)@@G@@        . RETURN  @B@@@FASG       J         0                 .   @ @@@FDW
)@@G@@          DL        A0,BLANKS @D@@@F          DS        A0,IOPKT        DX
)@@G@@  . BLANK PACKET  @E@@@F          L         A0,*0,X11         . GET UNOTDY
)@@G@@ NUMBER     @E@@@F          DSL       A0,36             . SHIFT FOR THE DZ
)@@G@@DIVIDE@E@@@F          DI,U      A0,10             . CONVERT TO BINARY   EA
)@@G@@@E@@@F          JZ        A0,ASG1           . JUMP ON ONE LETTER  @F@@@FEB
)@@G@@          LSSL      A0,6              . SHIFT A0 FOR NEXT ADD     @E@@@FEC
)@@G@@          A,U       A0,'00',A1        . CONVERT TO FIELDATA @D@@@F      ED
)@@G@@    S,T1      A0,IOPKT          . SET IN PACKET @C@@@F          J       EE
)@@G@@  ASG2              . CONTINUE@E@@@FASG1      A,U       A1,'0'          EF
)@@G@@  . CONVERT TO FIELDATA @B@@@F          S,S1      A1,IOPKT          .   EG
)@@G@@@E@@@FASG2      L,U       A0,IOPKT          . GET PACKET ADDRESS  @E@@@FEH
)@@G@@          ER        FACIT$            . CHECK THE FACILITIES@E@@@F      EI
)@@G@@    TNZ,S1    IOPKT+6           . IS FILE ASSIGNED    @D@@@F          J EJ
)@@G@@        ASG4              . NO, TELL TIM  @B@@@FASG3      SZ        IOPKEK
)@@G@@T+3           .   @E@@@F          SZ        FUNC              . CLEAR THEL
)@@G@@E PACKER    @C@@@F          J         ASG               . RETURN  @[@@@FEM
)@@G@@ASG4. @D@@@F          L         A0,IOPKT          . GET FILENAME  @E@@@FEN
)@@G@@          S         A0,NA             . STORE IN MESSAGE    @E@@@F      EO
)@@G@@    L         A0,(P 01,LNA,NA)  . GET THE MESSAGE     @E@@@F          EREP
)@@G@@        PRINT$            .  UNIT NOT ASSIGNED  @C@@@F          ER      EQ
)@@G@@  ERR$              . GO AWAY @[@@@G.     @[@@@G.     @F@@@G. FIND OUT IER
)@@G@@F THE TAPE WE ARE ABOUT TO WRITE ON IS LABELED BY     @B@@@G. PERFORMINGES
)@@G@@ THE FOLLOWING ALGORITHM:     @E@@@G. DO ER FITEM$ TO FIND OUT IF TLS ISET
)@@G@@ TURNED ON IN THE EXEC. @F@@@G. THEN DO ER TLBL$ WITH SUBFUNCTION 020 (WEU
)@@G@@RITE HDR1&2) SPECIFYING @D@@@G. A PACKET WWITH "NO CHANGE" TO THE EXISTIEV
)@@G@@NG PCT ITEM.@F@@@G. IF THE ERROR STATUS RETURNED IS 016, THE TAPE IS UNLEW
)@@G@@ABELED.     @F@@@G. IN ANY OTHER CASE (INCLUDING NORMAL RETURN) THE TAPEEX
)@@G@@ IS LABELED.@C@@@GISLABL*   . LOGICAL FUNCTION ISLABL(UNITNUMBER) @D@@@IEY
)@@G@@          S         X11,SAVEX11       . FOR DEBUG     @]@H@G SLJ TON$   EZ
)@@G@@@F@@@G          TZ        NOUT              . IS THERE AN OUTPUT TAPE?  FA
)@@G@@@I@@@G          J         LBLD              . ASSUME NONEXISTANT OUTPUT FB
)@@G@@TAPE IS UNLABE    @D@@@G          TP        IOPKT+3           . IF NECESFC
)@@G@@SARY, @F@@@G          ER        WAIT$             . WAIT FOR IO TO COMPLFD
)@@G@@ETE   @E@@@G          TNZ       IOPKT             . IS FILE ASSIGNED?   FE
)@@G@@@C@@@G          SLJ       ASG               . NOPE.   @F@@@G          DLFF
)@@G@@        A0,IOPKT          . MOVE FILE NAME TO PACKETS @ @@@G          DSFG
)@@G@@        A0,FITPKT @B@@@G          DS        A0,TLSPKT+1       .   @E@@@GFH
)@@G@@          L         A0,(13,FITPKT)    . GET FITEM$ INFO     @ @@@H      FI
)@@G@@    ER        FITEM$    @G@@@G          TN        FITPKT+7          . ISFJ
)@@G@@ TLS TURNED ON IN THIS EXEC?  @C@@@G          J         NOTLBL          FK
)@@G@@  . NOPE    @D@@@G          L         A0,(3,TLSPKT)     . TRY ER TLBL$  FL
)@@G@@@B@@@G          ER        TLBL$             .   @E@@@G          S       FM
)@@G@@  A0,TLBSTAT        . SAVE FOR DEBUGGING  @F@@@G          JN        A0,IFN
)@@G@@NTERP         . INTERPRET ERROR STATUS    @G@@@GLBLD      L,U       A0,1FO
)@@G@@              . SUCCEEDED - MUST BE LABELED.    @E@@@G          J       FP
)@@G@@  2,X11             . RETURN ".TRUE."     @D@@@GNOTLBL    L,U       A0,0FQ
)@@G@@              . NOT LABELED.  @E@@@G          J         2,X11           FR
)@@G@@  . RETURN ".FALSE."    @[@@@GINTERP@F@@@G          L,S3      A0,TLBSTATFS
)@@G@@        . GET STATUS RELEVENT INFO  @D@@@G          TNE,U     A0,016    FT
)@@G@@        . UNLABELED?    @C@@@G          J         NOTLBL            . YEFU
)@@G@@S.    @G@@@G          J         LBLD              . NO - SOME OTHER PROBFV
)@@G@@LEM THAT    @F@@@G                                      . DOESNT CONCERNFW
)@@G@@ US HERE.   @[@@@F.     @#@@@F. COMMON AREA     @[@@@F.     @^@@@FFLAGS FX
)@@G@@    INFO      2 20@[@@@F$(20).@D@@@FUIN       RES       1               FY
)@@G@@  . INPUT UNIT    @E@@@FUOUT      RES       1                 . OUTPUT UFZ
)@@G@@NIT- BINARY @E@@@FNOUT      RES       1                 . LOGICAL OUTPUTGA
)@@G@@ UNIT @B@@@FTWOEOF    RES       1                 .   @B@@@FEOFS      REGB
)@@G@@S       1                 .   @F@@@JREC       RES       1               GC
)@@G@@  . SET IF RECOVERY WANTED    @E@@@JREW       RES       1               GD
)@@G@@  . SET IF REWIND WANTED@G@@@JBUFSIZE   RES       1                 . SIGE
)@@G@@ZE OF BUFFER OFF END OF DBANK @[@@@F$(2). @D@@@ISAVEX11   +         0   GF
)@@G@@              . FOR DEBUG     @^@@@GFITPKT    RES       13  @D@@@GTLSPKTGG
)@@G@@    +         020               . WRITE HDR1&2  @^@@@G          RES     GH
)@@G@@  2   @F@@@GTLBSTAT   RES       1                 . TLBL$ STATUS RETURNEGI
)@@G@@D     @B@@@FBLANKS    '            '              .   @B@@@FIOPKT     + GJ
)@@G@@        0                 .   @B@@@F          +         0               GK
)@@G@@  .   @B@@@F          +         0                 .   @B@@@FFUNC      + GL
)@@G@@        0                 .   @B@@@FACWD      +         0               GM
)@@G@@  .   @B@@@F          RES       5                 .   @B@@@FNA        ' GN
)@@G@@      NOT ASSIGNED'       .   @B@@@FLNA       EQU       $-NA            GO
)@@G@@  .   @B@@@F          END                         .   ___       S,T1    GP
)@@G@@  A1,FUNC           . SET THE FUNCTION    @D@@@F*[S@@@*SDFF*@[@@@[$(1)  GQ
)@@G@@@^@@@[HCONT$*   J         1,11@]@@@]HCGTE$* .   @]@@@[HVRTN$*     @#@ @[GR
